    "created_at": "2012-10-12T17:38:51Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-10-12T17:38:51Z",
    "body": "I feel very strongly about this after working on Servo for a while. Most of our exploitable crashes are in safe code. If we don't do this I feel that Rust will, in a practical sense, have no more safety guarantees than C++.\n\nHow can a security auditor hope to audit Rust code if every single call could do wildly unsafe things?\n",
